      <th style="padding: 12px 16px; text-align: left;">Finance use case</th>
      <th style="padding: 12px 16px; text-align: left;">C2 use case</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0;">
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;"><strong>Immutability</strong></td>
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;">Transactions can't be reversed or censored</td>
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;">Commands can't be deleted or modified after broadcast</td>
    </tr>
    <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0;">
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;"><strong>Decentralisation</strong></td>
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;">No single point of failure in the network</td>
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;">No single server to seize; no hosting provider to contact</td>
    </tr>
    <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0;">
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;"><strong>Global accessibility</strong></td>
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;">Anyone can access the chain from anywhere</td>
      <td style="padding: 12px 16px;">Bots can reach C2 from any country through any ISP</td>
    </tr>
